But we won't call those other guys losers but Jacobellis somehow is a loser? Give me a break! They are now in unhappy relationships, overweight and addicted. Nobody criticises them. Jacobellis, on the other hand, achieved more at the age of 20 than most people ever would in an entire lifetime. Yet, she receives lots of hate.

What if people were not such oxygen thiefs, but actually supportive and understanding? What if people tried to encourage her to continue and what if US Americans actually thanked her for still bringing home silver?

comments.text: Excellent doc! My fav athlete of all time! Quick story: My dad and I collect sports cards and we pulled a signed card of Jacobellis from a pack about a month before the 2014 olympics. We didnt know much about her but soon I realized she was the girl who fell and got silver. Then out of nowhere my dad had a stroke and had to be put in the hospital for, 4 or 5 days i think, hes doing well nowadays thankfully. The first day he was gone was the qualification round and I remember watching the livestream all night just to watch her race. She won and looked fantastic, then the next day she fell and it was honestly crushing. I remember crying because that was about the only thing I could care about that got me not so worried about my dad. Fast forward to 2022 I remember watching the snowboard cross final with my college roommate. I explained to him why I couldnt believe she was even still competing but it made sense because she was always super inspiring and I knew she wanted that gold more than anything. We celebrated her win, the coolest part was that he was super happy that an American won but he didnt know her as the girl that fell 18 years earlier, just saw her as the champ. Thanks for reading of you made it this far, never give up because you never know who you will inspire!!! Much love

This is the snowboarding equivalent to the yips. It sucks that one mistake cost her so much, and all of her falls were being caused by her brain constantly reminding her about the one that started it all and how she cant do it again.
